^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|First let me discuss possible bids by Ruth. There are 2 theories about how to bid 6-4 hands. One is you bid your 6 card suit, then your 4 card suit, then your 6 card suit. Some people call this "6-4-6." The other choice is "6-6-4"—you rebid your 6 card suit then show you 4 card suit. |
PG| ***** 60 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|When your suit is a major, I prefer "6-6-4" because I think it is more important to show your 6 card major than a 4 card minor. The only exception to that is when I have 6 spades and 4 hearts and it goes for example 1S-P-2C-P-?. I will rebid 2@H rather than show my 6th spade. However, in general I prefer to rebid my 6 card major.|
